fileChanges.details:
Lines 146-155: Currently the code manually fetches alt text with `get_post_meta($featuredImageId, '_wp_attachment_image_alt', true)` then passes `'alt' => $img_alt ?: ''` to wp_get_attachment_image(). This is redundant because wp_get_attachment_image() already reads the media library alt text automatically. The override with `?: ''` was incorrectly clearing alt text when none was set.

Change: Remove the manual `$img_alt` lookup (line 146) and remove the `'alt'` key from the attributes array passed to wp_get_attachment_image(). This lets WordPress handle alt text natively -- it will use whatever alt text is set in the media library.

Before:
```php
$img_alt = get_post_meta( $featuredImageId, '_wp_attachment_image_alt', true );
echo wp_get_attachment_image(
    $featuredImageId,
    'full',
    false,
    [
        'class' => 'w-full h-full object-cover',
        'alt'   => $img_alt ?: '',
    ]
);
```

After:
```php
echo wp_get_attachment_image(
    $featuredImageId,
    'full',
    false,
    [
        'class' => 'w-full h-full object-cover',
    ]
);
```
